==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''bīdan'', Old High German [[bitan|bītan]], Old Norse [[bíða]] (Swedish [[bida]]), Gothic [[𐌱𐌴𐌹𐌳𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'bi:dan/

===Verb===
'''bīdan''' (class I strong)
# to [[wait]], to wait for; to [[stay]]

